Calling the Symfony\Component\EventDispatcher\EventDispatcherInterface::dispatch() method with a string event name as the first argument is deprecated in drupal:9.1.0, an Event object will be required instead in drupal:10.0.0. See https://www.drupal.org/node/3154407
The "app.root" service is deprecated in drupal:9.0.0 and is removed from drupal:10.0.0. Use the app.root parameter instead. See https://www.drupal.org/node/3080612
The "Symfony\Component\HttpKernel\Event\GetResponseForExceptionEvent::getException()" method is deprecated since Symfony 4.4, use "getThrowable()" instead.
Non-object services are deprecated since Symfony 4.4, please fix the "app.root" service which is of type "string" right now.
The "app.root.factory" service is deprecated in drupal:9.0.0 and is removed from drupal:10.0.0. Use the app.root parameter instead. See https://www.drupal.org/node/3080612
The "Drupal\Tests\Listeners\DrupalListener" class implements "PHPUnit\Framework\TestListener" that is deprecated.
